## 0.2.25

- **Fix: bundles xcespserver 0.2.13** — two SNMP / status fixes:

  1. **IF-MIB::ifTable now correctly overrides the master snmpd's
     built-in handler.**  0.2.22 shipped the subagent registration
     at the net-snmp default priority (127), which TIES with the
     built-in `mibII/interfaces` module — master kept its own and
     `IF-MIB::ifTable` walks returned the host's kernel interfaces
     (lo, ens160, …) instead of the XCESP router/vrf/interface
     rows.  Now registers at priority 5 (lower = higher precedence
     per AgentX) and wins regardless of master configuration.

  2. **`show server` now reports the fresh BackupSW version
     immediately after `copy sw latest backup-sw`** (was: stale
     until next xcespserver restart).  FileActionHandler pushes
     the new value into ServerStatus right after the tarball
     extracts.

