## 0.2.21

- **Fix: SNMP feature didn't work on Fedora.**  Two packaging
  assumptions were wrong:

  1. Fedora's stock `/etc/snmp/snmpd.conf` does **not** auto-include
     `/etc/snmp/snmpd.conf.d/` (Debian's does).  The 0.2.20 drop-in
     was silently ignored, snmpd never enabled AgentX, the
     `/var/agentx/master` socket never appeared, and xcespserver's
     embedded subagent looped forever with `Failed to connect to
     the agentx master agent`.

  2. Fedora's net-snmp 5.9.4 rejects `agentXPerms 0660 0660 root
     xcesp` with `Can't identify user (root).` and falls back to
     creating the socket as `root:root mode 0755` — unreachable
     from the `xcesp` uid.

  `xcesp-activate` now does two things instead:

  - Writes a managed marker block (`# BEGIN xcesp-snmp` / `# END
    xcesp-snmp`) into `/etc/snmp/snmpd.conf` itself with the
    `master agentx` + `agentXSocket` lines.  Same pattern used for
    `/etc/pam.d/sshd`.  Works on every distro since we no longer
    rely on conf.d auto-inclusion.
  - Writes a systemd drop-in at
    `/etc/systemd/system/snmpd.service.d/xcesp.conf` with
    `ExecStartPost=chgrp xcesp + chmod 0660 /var/agentx/master`.
    Fires after snmpd creates the socket; idempotent and harmless
    if the socket isn't there yet.

  Teardown (operator flips `enabled false`) strips the marker
  block, removes the systemd drop-in, does daemon-reload, restarts
  snmpd.

  Legacy cleanup: the 0.2.20-era `/etc/snmp/snmpd.conf.d/xcesp.conf`
  is removed on every activation, so upgrading from 0.2.20 leaves a
  clean slate before the new pattern goes in.

  The `cfg/xcesp-snmpd.conf` file is still shipped (in the tarball
  and at `/var/xcesp/mainsw/cfg/`) for documentation; it is no
  longer read by xcesp-activate.

  No xcespserver / xcespcli rebuild required — install.sh-side
  change only.

## 0.2.20

- **Hotfix: SNMP feature was inert in 0.2.19.**  `xcesp-snmpd.conf`
  was bundled into the tarball but `install.sh` never copied it to
  `$MAINSW_DIR/cfg/xcesp-snmpd.conf` where `xcesp-activate` looks for
  it.  Operators saw `AAA: SNMP requested but
  /var/xcesp/mainsw/cfg/xcesp-snmpd.conf missing — skipping`, the
  snmpd drop-in was never installed, snmpd never enabled AgentX, the
  /var/agentx/master socket never appeared, and xcespserver's
  embedded subagent looped forever with
  `Failed to connect to the agentx master agent`.

  Added a `Managed-asset configs → mainsw/cfg/` install step that
  copies `xcesp-snmpd.conf` into `$MAINSW_DIR/cfg/`.  Now refreshed
  on every package install, like binaries and schema.

  No xcespserver / xcespcli rebuild required — this is install.sh
  only.

