## 0.2.18

- **Hotfix: audit feature was inert in 0.2.17.**  The audit policy
  file was written to `/etc/xcesp/audit.conf`, but xcespserver runs
  as the `xcesp` uid (non-root) and silently failed to write under
  `/etc/`.  xcespcli read the missing file as "audit off" regardless
  of the operator's `audit enabled true` commit.

  Moved the policy file to `/var/lib/xcesp/audit.conf` — same
  directory as managed-users.state and aaa-config.state, owned
  `root:xcesp 2775` (writable by xcespserver, readable by every
  xcespcli session).

  Bundles xcespserver 0.2.9 (corrected writer path) and xcespcli
  0.2.8 (corrected reader path).

