## 0.2.17

- **Audit feature default flipped off.**  `management/aaa/audit/enabled`
  schema default `true` → `false`.  0.2.16 emitted audit records
  unconditionally (the knob was a placeholder); 0.2.17 honours it as
  a real opt-in toggle.  Operators who want audit must add:

      management
        aaa
          audit
            enabled true
          !
        !
      !

  Bundles xcespserver 0.2.8 (publishes `/etc/xcesp/audit.conf` at
  every commit) and xcespcli 0.2.7 (reads `/etc/xcesp/audit.conf` in
  CliSession's constructor and short-circuits `emitAuditLog()` when
  `enabled = false`).

- **Fix: xcesp-login now passes `--audit-user` to xcespcli.**  In
  0.2.16 the script set `audit_user` from `XCESP_AUDIT_USER` but
  didn't pass it on the command line, so TACACS+/RADIUS audit lines
  showed the pool account name (`xcesp-tacacs` / `xcesp-radius`)
  instead of the centrally-authenticated identity.  The passthrough
  was waiting for xcespcli to ship `--audit-user`, which landed in
  0.2.6.

