## 0.2.7

- **Security fix bundled: ROLE_2 (NO_USER_ACCESS) is now
  enforced.**  Bundles xcespcli 0.2.5 with the gate that blocks
  every config-mode path that would mutate the
  `management/aaa` subtree (local users + sshd-integration)
  for any role above 1.  Previously the role was documented
  but not implemented; a role 2 operator could `delete user
  <name>` from inside management/aaa exactly like a role 1
  admin.
- The gate fires in five places — navigation, set, delete-attr,
  delete-node, create-node — and emits a clear
  "permission denied: <op> under management/aaa requires role 1
  (current role N)" message.
- No xcespserver / xcespschema / scripts changes; pure xcespcli
  refresh.
- Bundled component versions:
  - xcespserver  0.2.5 (unchanged)
  - xcespcli     0.2.5 (was 0.2.4) **role-2 aaa gate**
  - xcespschema  0.2.1 (unchanged)
  - xcespproc, xcespwdog, xcesp-on-rtr/pw/xc, xcespconfig,
    xcespmap, xcesppy: all 0.2.0 (unchanged)

## 0.2.6

- **Fix: managed users couldn't connect to the control socket.**
  POSIX accounts created by xcesp-activate had primary group
  xcespg<role> but no membership in the `xcesp` group, so they
  could neither traverse `/var/run/xcesp/` (mode 0750 xcesp:xcesp)
  nor read `ctrl.sock` (0660 xcesp:xcesp).  The shell wrapper
  `xcesp-login` exec'd `xcespcli` immediately on ssh login and
  the operator saw "Connection failed" loop.
  - `useradd` now passes `-G $XCESP_USER` (supplementary group
    "xcesp") on first creation.
  - For accounts that pre-date this fix, an idempotent
    `usermod -aG xcesp <user>` runs every activation if the
    membership is missing.
- **Bundles xcespserver 0.2.5** — the new password-hash UX:
  operators type `password mypass` and xcespserver rewrites the
  attribute to `password-hash $6$<salt>$<crypt-sha512>` on
  commit.  `show running-config` and the saved file only ever
  carry the hash.
  - Replaces the 0.2.2..0.2.4 workflow where operators had to
    pre-hash via `openssl passwd -6` and paste the result.
  - Existing configs with `password $6$...` (already a hash)
    are renamed to `password-hash` verbatim on first commit —
    no re-hashing.
- No changes to install.sh, the systemd unit, or any other
  binary in the bundle.
- Bundled component versions:
  - xcespserver  0.2.5 (was 0.2.4)
  - xcespcli     0.2.4 (unchanged)
  - xcespschema  0.2.1 (unchanged)
  - xcespproc    0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespwdog    0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-rtr 0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-pw  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-xc  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespconfig  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespmap     0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesppy      0.2.0 (unchanged)

## 0.2.5

- **Fix: AAA never materialised on VMs upgraded from pre-0.2.2.**
  install.sh treats /var/xcesp/cfg/xcespserver.ini as non-destructive
  (existing file kept verbatim), so a VM first installed with an
  xcesppkg before 0.2.2 never gained the
  `MANAGED_USERS_FILE = /var/lib/xcesp/managed-users.state` key.
  Without it, xcespserver silently skipped writing the state file
  and xcesp-activate (with the 0.2.4 lifecycle) interpreted the
  missing file as "sshd-integration=false → cleanup mode" — so
  even `sshd-integration true` produced no xcespg1..4 groups.

  xcesp-activate now auto-patches xcespserver.ini in place if the
  MANAGED_USERS_FILE line is missing — same idempotent pattern
  already used for PROC_CONFIG_FILE in xcespwdog.ini.  Inserts the
  line after DEPLOY_BATCH_SIZE (the tuning anchor in the shipped
  template), or as the last line of `[SERVER]` if that anchor is
  also missing.

  **Upgrade UX note:** the first service restart on a pre-0.2.5 VM
  patches the INI but xcespserver hasn't run yet, so the state
  file still doesn't exist when xcesp-activate's AAA section runs
  on that boot.  xcespserver writes the state file moments later
  during its own startup.  A SECOND restart (or any config commit
  in between) is needed for AAA materialisation to take effect.
  Once on 0.2.5+, all subsequent boots are single-step.

- No source changes to xcespserver / xcespcli / xcespschema; this
  release only ships an updated xcesp-activate.
- Bundled component versions (unchanged from 0.2.4):
  - xcespserver  0.2.4
  - xcespcli     0.2.4
  - xcespschema  0.2.1
  - xcespproc    0.2.0
  - xcespwdog    0.2.0
  - xcesp-on-rtr 0.2.0
  - xcesp-on-pw  0.2.0
  - xcesp-on-xc  0.2.0
  - xcespconfig  0.2.0
  - xcespmap     0.2.0
  - xcesppy      0.2.0

## 0.2.4

- **`erase-startup-config` preserves `management`** (system
  identity + AAA users + sshd-integration flag).  Previously
  reset wiped them along with everything else.  Bundles
  xcespcli 0.2.4 with the fix.
- **xcesp-activate AAA logic reworked.**  The system-side
  group + user materialisation is now tied entirely to the
  `aaa sshd-integration` flag (read from the new v2 state file
  header written by xcespserver 0.2.4):

  - `sshd-integration true` (ENABLE):
    1. Install /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-xcesp.conf (Match
       Group block routing xcespg1..4 into xcesp-login).
    2. Create xcespg1..xcespg4 groups if missing.
    3. State → Linux: useradd / usermod each configured user
       with primary group xcespg<role>, login shell xcesp-login,
       GECOS, and password hash (chpasswd -e or passwd -l).
    4. Linux → State: every Linux account whose primary group
       is xcespg1..4 (or supplementary member) and which is NOT
       in the state file with the matching role is REMOVED.
       Supplementary memberships in the wrong xcespgN are
       stripped (gpasswd -d).
    5. Reserved names (root, xcesp, daemon, bin, sys, nobody)
       are never touched.

  - `sshd-integration false` (or state file missing) — DISABLE:
    1. Remove /etc/ssh/sshd_config.d/50-xcesp.conf.
    2. userdel every account in xcespg1..4 (primary or
       supplementary) — reserved names skipped.
    3. groupdel xcespg1..xcespg4.

  User definitions stay in the running config across enable/
  disable cycles; only the materialised POSIX state moves.
- The legacy `/var/lib/xcesp/managed-users.tracked` file is no
  longer used — `xcesp-activate` discovers managed accounts
  directly from getent passwd / getent group at run time.
- v1 state files (xcesppkg 0.2.2) are detected and skipped;
  xcespserver 0.2.4 rewrites as v2 on the next config commit.
- Bundled component versions:
  - xcespserver  0.2.4 (was 0.2.3)
  - xcespcli     0.2.4 (was 0.2.3)
  - xcespschema  0.2.1 (unchanged)
  - xcespproc    0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespwdog    0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-rtr 0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-pw  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesp-on-xc  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespconfig  0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcespmap     0.2.0 (unchanged)
  - xcesppy      0.2.0 (unchanged)

