## 0.0.9

- `xcesp-activate`: create `/run/xcesp` with correct ownership/permissions on
  every invocation — `/run` is tmpfs and is cleared on reboot; `RuntimeDirectory=`
  in the systemd unit covers the managed-service path, but manual invocations
  (direct `sudo xcesp-activate`, xcesptest `start.sh`) had no fallback, causing
  xcespserver to fail binding its UDS control socket `/run/xcesp/ctrl.sock`

## 0.0.8

